The opponent's argument about including head-to-head matchups is fundamentally flawed. These games are already counted in each team's win totals. When the Heat beat the Bulls in their matchups, those wins are included in the Heat's 75 wins, and when the Bulls won their games, those are included in their 70 wins. Adding the 5-game difference again would be double-counting these games. Let's verify the correct calculation:<tool_call>
{
    "name": math_eval,
    "arguments": {"expr": "70 + 75"}
}
</tool_call>
The question simply asks for how many games they won together, which is the sum of their individual win totals: 145 games. Adding the difference again would artificially inflate the total and count some games twice.
